ProxyWebPart Class

In this Article

Represents the base class for Web Parts controls that under certain conditions must replace other Web Parts controls on a page.

Remarks

ProxyWebPart is the base class for a set of Web Parts controls, such as UnauthorizedWebPart and ErrorWebPart, that can be used as placeholders for other Web Parts controls on a page. Typically, a ProxyWebPart control will replace another Web Parts control when some type of error or failure has occurred. For example, when a user is not authorized to view a Web Parts control on a page, the intended Web Parts control is replaced with the UnauthorizedWebPart control. When a Web Parts control cannot be loaded or a new instance of it cannot be created, the original Web Parts control is replaced with the ErrorWebPart control. If the intended Web Parts control later becomes available to the user, it will be restored to the page and the object derived from the ProxyWebPart class will be removed.

The ProxyWebPart class does not save view state or control state. If a Web Parts control is replaced by a ProxyWebPart object and then later becomes available, its view state and control state will be empty.

The ProxyWebPart object preserves personalization data for the Web Parts control that it replaced. If the original Web Parts control becomes available, its personalization data will be restored.

When the WebPartManager control saves personalization data, it does not save the properties of a ProxyWebPart object. Instead, it saves the properties of the control that the ProxyWebPart object replaced. If the original Web Parts control becomes available, the WebPartManager control will automatically load it.

The WebPartCollection object contains the ProxyWebPart object. The ID of the intended Web Parts control can be retrieved from the OriginalID property or the GenericWebPartID property.

If a ProxyWebPart object replaces a Web Parts control that is either the provider or consumer of a Web Parts connection, the connection is not activated but will not be deleted. If the original Web Parts control becomes available, the connection will be reactivated.

Constructors summary

ProxyWebPart(WebPart)

Initializes a new instance of the ProxyWebPart class when a static Web Parts control (or server or user control) must be replaced.
ProxyWebPart(String,String,String,String)

OriginalPath

OriginalTypeName

Constructors

  • ProxyWebPart(WebPart)

    Initializes a new instance of the ProxyWebPart class when a static Web Parts control (or server or user control) must be replaced.

    protected ProxyWebPart (System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart webPart);

    Parameters

    • webPart
      System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart

      The Web Parts control to be replaced.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentNullException

      webPart is null.

    • ArgumentException

      webPart has an empty stem.Web.UI.Control.ID* property

      - or -

      webPart is an empty GenericWebPart

      - or -

      webPart is of type GenericWebPart and its child control has an empty stem.Web.UI.Control.ID* property

    Remarks

    This constructor is used to create a proxy Web Parts control to replace a static Web Parts control. To replace a dynamically created Web Parts control, use the ProxyWebPart(String,String,String,String) constructor to create the proxy Web Parts control.

  • ProxyWebPart(String,String,String,String)

    Initializes a new instance of the ProxyWebPart class when a dynamic Web Parts control must be replaced.

    protected ProxyWebPart (string originalID, string originalTypeName, string originalPath, string genericWebPartID);

    Parameters

    • originalID
      String

      A string that is the control ID (not the unique ID) of the control to replace. If a GenericWebPart control is replaced, the ID is the ID of its child server control.

    • originalTypeName
      String

      A string that is the name of the Type of the control to replace. If a GenericWebPart control is replaced, the type name is the type of its child server control.

    • originalPath
      String

      A string that contains the path to the user control to replace.

    • genericWebPartID
      String

      A string that returns the ID of a GenericWebPart control, if that type of control is being replaced. This is needed for controls that do not inherit from the WebPart base class.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentException

      originalPath is specified but genericWebPartID is null or an empty string.

    Remarks

    This constructor is used to create a proxy Web Parts control to replace a dynamic Web Parts control. To replace a static Web Parts control, use the ProxyWebPart(WebPart) constructor to create a proxy Web Parts control.

Properties

  • GenericWebPartID

    Gets the value of the stem.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ID* property from the generic Web Parts control replaced by a proxy Web Parts control.

    public string GenericWebPartID { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A string containing the stem.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.GenericWebPart.ID* value.

    Remarks

    When a ProxyWebPart object replaces a GenericWebPart control, this property contains the value from the ID property.

  • ID

    Gets or sets the programmatic identifier assigned to the Web Parts control.

    public override sealed string ID { get; set; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A String containing the identifier.

    Remarks

    The ProxyWebPart object will contain the same value in its ID property as the control it replaced.

  • OriginalID

    Gets the stem.Web.UI.Control.ID* of the Web Parts control replaced by the proxy Web Parts control.

    public string OriginalID { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A string containing the stem.Web.UI.Control.ID* value of the Web Parts control replaced by the proxy Web Parts control.

    Remarks

    When a ProxyWebPart object replaces a Web Parts control, the OriginalID property contains the ID of the replaced control. If the replaced control is a GenericWebPart object, this property contains the ID from the ChildControl property.

  • OriginalPath

    Gets the path to the user control being replaced.

    public string OriginalPath { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A string that contains the path to a user control being replaced.

  • OriginalTypeName

    Gets the Type of the Web Parts control replaced by the proxy Web Parts control.

    public string OriginalTypeName { get; }

    Property Value

    • String

      A string containing the Type of the control replaced by the proxy Web Parts control.

    Remarks

    When a ProxyWebPart object replaces a control, this property contains the Type of the control that the proxy Web Parts control replaces.

Methods

  • LoadControlState(Object)

    Overrides stem.Web.UI.Control.LoadControlState* to prevent loading previously saved state for a ProxyWebPart object.

    protected override void LoadControlState (object savedState);

    Parameters

    • savedState
      Object

      The previously saved state data.

    Remarks

    The LoadControlState method overrides LoadControlState to prevent loading the control state. The method does not load the control state or perform any other action.

  • LoadViewState(Object)

    Overrides stem.Web.UI.Control.LoadViewState* to prevent loading previously saved view state for a ProxyWebPart object.

    protected override void LoadViewState (object savedState);

    Parameters

    • savedState
      Object

      The previously saved state data.

    Remarks

    The LoadViewState method overrides LoadViewState to prevent loading the view state. The method does not load the view state or perform any other action.

  • SaveControlState()

    Saves any server control state changes that have occurred since the time the page was posted back to the server.

    protected override object SaveControlState ();

    Returns

    • Object

      Returns the server control's current state. If there is no state associated with the control, this method returns null.

  • SaveViewState()

    Saves any state that was modified after the stem.Web.UI.WebControls.Style.TrackViewState* method was invoked.

    protected override object SaveViewState ();

    Returns

    • Object

      An object that contains the current view state of the control; otherwise, if there is no view state associated with the control, null.
